snippet.textDisplay:
Man Aamadam is an Afghan song and sung  by Iranian singer Gogosh. An 
Afghan singer, writer , and musician  Dr. Zaland wrote and composed (man
 Aamadam ) song which means (I have come to you)
In early 70 when Gogosh was performing a concert in Afghanistan Dr. Zaland gifted this song to her. Then in the early 80s the song was sung by Ashbunsly (dil koya koys gulsom)This is not persion song but Dari is the old and pure version of Farsi and it is Afghanistan's second  language.
